    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Crankcase, Crankshaft, and
        Camshaft - Installation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Installation</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="4">
            <title>Camshaft Bushings</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Identify each camshaft bushing according to its outside diameter. See camshaft bushing
                    <hotlnk document="eges3351_426.xml" xrefid="t335001601">Specifications</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="t335001601"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3350016519" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figk03/K03010.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Camshaft Bushing Puller (installer)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Backup nut</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Expanding collet</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Puller screw extension</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Puller shaft</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new camshaft bushing on the
                    <hotlnk document="eges3351_428.xml" xrefid="t335001603">Camshaft Bushing Puller</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="t335001603"/>
                    expanding collet.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten expanding collet by turning backup nut until camshaft bushing is held
                    securely.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3350016520" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg5/EG5247.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Camshaft bearing oil hole location mark</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mark each camshaft bushing oil hole location on the backup nut of the Camshaft Bushing
                    Puller to help align bushing oil hole with the crankcase oil hole.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, camshaft bushing oil holes must align with crankcase oil holes.
                    </para>
                </caution>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, camshaft bushings must be installed in the proper order due to
                        different outside diameters. Both intermediate camshaft bushings have an outer diameter slightly
                        smaller than bushings used in the front and rear.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f3350016521" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figK03/K03011.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Camshaft bushing installation pull direction (partial crankcase cut-away)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Front of engine</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Crankcase assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Front and rear camshaft bushings</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Intermediate camshaft bushings</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Camshaft seal ring</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install rear intermediate bushing through the rear of the crankcase.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pull bushing in place from the front of the crankcase by turning the pulling nut on the
                    puller screw.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the Camshaft Bushing Puller and inspect camshaft bushing oil hole to crankcase
                    oil hole alignment.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the front intermediate bushing through the front of the crankcase.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pull bushing in place from the rear of the crankcase by turning the pulling nut on the
                    puller screw.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the Camshaft Bushing Puller and inspect camshaft bushing oil hole to crankcase
                    oil hole alignment.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3350016522" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figk03/K03012.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Front camshaft bushing installation</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Front camshaft bushing</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Crankcase oil hole alignment mark</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Camshaft bushing oil hole</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Camshaft Bushing Puller (installer)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Camshaft bushing oil hole alignment mark</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the front camshaft bushing through the front of the crankcase.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pull bushing in place from the rear of the crankcase by turning the pulling nut on the
                    puller screw.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the Camshaft Bushing Puller and inspect camshaft bushing oil hole to crankcase
                    oil hole alignment.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the rear bushing through the rear of the crankcase.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pull the bushing in place from the front of the crankcase by turning the pulling nut on
                    the puller screw.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the Camshaft Bushing Puller and inspect camshaft bushing oil hole to crankcase
                    oil hole alignment.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install camshaft seal ring in rear of crankcase.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
